<div id="install" class="installation">
    <p>Just unzip the file you downloaded, in the directory (e.g. <code class="dirName">neo4j-community-1.8</code>) you&#39;ll find:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>configuration files under <code>conf/</code></li>
        <li>database files under <code>data/graph.db</code></li>
        <li>log files under <code>data/log</code> and <code>data/graph.db/messages.log</code></li>
        <li>start- and other scripts under <code>bin/</code></li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>Starting Neo4j on Linux, OS X and Unix</h2>
    <p>Start Neo4j Server with <code>bin/neo4j start</code> in a command line console or terminal of your choice, <br/>
        then open <a href="http://localhost:7474" target="_blank"><code>http://localhost:7474</code></a> for the Web UI.</p>
    
